---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SOCIAL_LINKS } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title="Work & Projects | Joe Karlsson" description="Joe Karlsson's projects, demos, open source work, and portfolio.">
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-8">
		<h1 class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold text-coral md:text-4xl">Work & Projects</h1>
		<p class="mb-10 text-gray-400">
			I build things — software, hardware, IoT contraptions, and the occasional questionable idea.
			Here's a collection of projects I've shipped over the years.
		</p>

		<!-- IoT & Hardware -->
		<h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-teal">IoT & Hardware</h2>
		<div class="mb-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/iot-kitty-litter-box" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-teal/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-teal/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/iot-litter-box.png" alt="IoT Kitty Litter Box" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-teal">IoT Kitty Litter Box</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">25 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Welcome to the Internet of Toilets. An IoT-connected cat litter box built with a Raspberry Pi, weight sensors, and Node.js. Monitors usage patterns and sends notifications. Became one of my most popular conference talks — presented at 20+ events worldwide.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-teal/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-teal/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/magic-mirror.jpeg" alt="MagicMirror Smart Mirror" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-teal">MagicMirror² — Smart IoT Mirror</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">A smart mirror built with a Raspberry Pi running MagicMirror² software behind a two-way mirror. Displays weather, calendar, news, and Home Assistant integrations. Still running in my house today.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-teal/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-teal/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/moodlite.png" alt="Moodlite Smart Light Panels" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-teal">Moodlite — Smart IoT Light Panels</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">DIY smart light panels inspired by Nanoleaf, built with 3D-printed housings, WS2812B LED strips, and an ESP8266. Controllable via MQTT and Home Assistant. A fun weekend project that turned into a deep dive into embedded systems.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="/blog/from-digital-design-to-real-world-object-creating-a-3d-printed-postcard-planter-rack/" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-teal/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-teal/10">
				<img src="/images/blog/from-digital-design-to-real-world-object-creating-a-3d-printed-postcard-planter-rack/Postcard-Rack-Planter.jpg" alt="3D Printed Planter" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-teal">3D-Printed Postcard Rack Planter</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Custom 3D-printed planter insert designed in Fusion 360 for a recycled postcard rack. Printed on my Prusa MK3. A fun exercise in turning digital design into a real-world object.</p>
				</div>
			</a>
		</div>

		<!-- Web & Software -->
		<h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-lavender">Web & Software</h2>
		<div class="mb-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/react-spotify-player" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-lavender/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-lavender/10">
				<img src="/images/blog/how-to-build-a-spotify-player-with-react-in-15-minutes/1_KGOTMV8KD120TApnijDauQ.png" alt="React Spotify Player" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-lavender">React Spotify Player</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">131 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">A real-time Spotify player built with React. My most starred open source project. Integrates with the Spotify Web API for custom playback. Accompanied a popular tutorial.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/bechdel-test" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-lavender/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-lavender/10">
				<img src="/images/blog/bechdel-io-how-we-used-javascript-to-help-make-film-more-inclusive/Bechdel.io-Blog-Banner.png" alt="Bechdel.io" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-lavender">Bechdel.io</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">30 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Does your favorite film pass the Bechdel Test? Uses NLP to parse movie scripts and analyze gender representation in dialogue. Featured in multiple publications and conference talks.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/Pixelate" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-lavender/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-lavender/10">
				<img src="/images/blog/how-to-pixelate-images-with-html5-and-javascript/pixelate-demo.jpg" alt="Pixelate" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-lavender">Pixelate</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">15 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">HTML5 webapp that pixelates any image using the Canvas API. One of my early web projects that taught me a ton about image manipulation in the browser.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/night-out" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-lavender/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-lavender/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/launch-target.jpg" alt="Launch Target" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-lavender">Launch Target — Lunch Coordination</h3>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">A real-time coordination app to help you and your friends find a place to eat. Because deciding where to go for lunch is the hardest problem in computer science.</p>
				</div>
			</a>
		</div>

		<!-- Games & Fun -->
		<h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-pink">Games & Fun Stuff</h2>
		<div class="mb-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/wave-jump" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-pink/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-pink/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/wave-jump.png" alt="Wave Jump" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-pink">Wave Jump</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">5 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">An 80's arcade-inspired multiplayer browser game built with Phaser.js. Dodge waves and outlast your opponents.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/rose-hobart" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-pink/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-pink/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/rose-hobart.jpg" alt="Rose Hobart" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-pink">Rose Hobart</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">2 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">A digital humanities project exploring performativity in cinema. Inspired by Joseph Cornell's 1936 found footage film. Analyzes and visualizes narrative structure in film scripts.</p>
				</div>
			</a>
		</div>

		<!-- Developer Tools & Education -->
		<h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-terminal-yellow">Developer Tools & Education</h2>
		<div class="mb-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/data-structures" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/data-structures.png" alt="Data Structures" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">Data Structures & Algorithms in JS</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">185 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Common data structures and algorithms implemented in JavaScript. Created as teaching material when I was an instructor at DevLeague. Covers linked lists, trees, graphs, sorting, and more.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/complete-guide-to-client-server-communication" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">Guide to Client-Server Communication</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">43 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Every way a client and server communicate — HTTP, WebSockets, SSE, GraphQL, gRPC, and more. A comprehensive reference guide with examples.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/python-sudoku-generator-solver" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">Python Sudoku Generator & Solver</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">90 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Generates unique Sudoku boards across 4 difficulty levels with a built-in solver using backtracking.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/movie-script-scraper" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/movie-script-scraper.png" alt="Movie Script Scraper" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">Movie Script Scraper</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">11 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Scraper to retrieve movie scripts by genre or title from IMSDB. Built as a data pipeline for the Bechdel Test project.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/mongodb-graphql-demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">MongoDB GraphQL Demo</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">20 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Using the MongoDB GraphQL Endpoint with Apollo Client in React.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/watson-speech-to-text-telegram-chatbot" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">Watson Speech-to-Text Telegram Bot</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">6 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">IBM Watson powered chatbot that transcribes voice messages in Telegram.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/best-buy-product-locator-chrome-extension" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<img src="/images/projects/best-buy-chrome.png" alt="Best Buy Chrome Extension" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">Best Buy Product Locator Extension</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">3 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Chrome extension that tells you if a product is available for same-day pickup at your local Best Buy. Built during my time on the Best Buy engineering team.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/client-side-field-level-encryption-csfle-mongodb-node-demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-yellow/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-yellow/10">
				<div class="p-4">
					<div class="mb-1 flex items-center justify-between">
						<h3 class="font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-yellow">MongoDB CSFLE Demo</h3>
						<span class="text-xs text-gray-500">5 stars</span>
					</div>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Reference implementation of Client-Side Field Level Encryption in MongoDB with Node.js.</p>
				</div>
			</a>
		</div>

		<!-- Homelab -->
		<h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-terminal-green">Homelab</h2>
		<div class="mb-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
			<a href="/blog/how-to-get-started-building-a-homelab-server-in-2024/" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-green/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-green/10">
				<img src="/images/blog/how-to-get-started-building-a-homelab-server-in-2024/Homelab-Archiecture-1024x473.png" alt="Homelab" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-green">Proxmox Homelab Cluster</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">A 2-node Proxmox cluster running 30+ LXC containers and VMs. Self-hosted services include Plex, Home Assistant, Frigate NVR, Grafana, and more. 20Gbps LACP backbone. I wrote the guide.</p>
				</div>
			</a>

			<a href="/blog/i-replaced-my-smart-home-with-a-dumber-home-but-at-least-its-private/" class="group block overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 no-underline transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-terminal-green/30 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-terminal-green/10">
				<img src="/images/blog/i-replaced-my-smart-home-with-a-dumber-home-but-at-least-its-private/I-Replaced-My-Smart-Home-with-a-Dumber-Home-But-at-Least-Its-Private.png" alt="Smart Home" class="h-44 w-full object-cover transition-transform duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" loading="lazy" />
				<div class="p-4">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white group-hover:text-terminal-green">Private Smart Home</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Replaced Alexa with Home Assistant Voice. Local speech processing via Wyoming Whisper on GPU. Zigbee devices, Frigate camera AI, and zero cloud dependencies.</p>
				</div>
			</a>
		</div>

		<!-- All repos link -->
		<div class="mb-10 rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-6 text-center">
			<p class="mb-3 text-gray-400">Want to see everything?</p>
			<a
				href={SOCIAL_LINKS.github}
				target="_blank"
				rel="noopener"
				class="inline-block rounded-md bg-coral px-5 py-2.5 font-medium text-surface-0 no-underline hover:bg-teal"
			>
				View all repos on GitHub &rarr;
			</a>
		</div>

		<!-- Work History -->
		<details class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3" open>
			<summary class="cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 text-gray-400 hover:text-white">
				<span class="font-medium">Work History</span>
			</summary>
			<div class="space-y-4 px-6 pb-6">
				<div class="border-l-2 border-teal pl-4">
					<h3 class="font-semibold text-white">Developer Advocate — CloudQuery</h3>
					<span class="text-sm text-gray-500">2025 – Present</span>
					<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Developer relations and content for the open-source ELT framework. Creating demos, tutorials, and developer resources.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-l-2 border-coral pl-4">
					<h3 class="font-semibold text-white">Developer Advocate — Tinybird</h3>
					<span class="text-sm text-gray-500">2023 – 2025</span>
					<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Empowered developers building real-time analytics applications. Created documentation, demos, blog posts, webinars, and workshops.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-l-2 border-lavender pl-4">
					<h3 class="font-semibold text-white">Senior Developer Advocate — SingleStore</h3>
					<span class="text-sm text-gray-500">2021 – 2023</span>
					<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Led community conversations around scaling SQL workloads. Built demos and content for the distributed SQL database.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-l-2 border-terminal-green pl-4">
					<h3 class="font-semibold text-white">Senior Developer Advocate — MongoDB</h3>
					<span class="text-sm text-gray-500">2019 – 2021</span>
					<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Built developer community, created tutorials, demos, and educational content. Subject matter expert for developer experience.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-l-2 border-sky pl-4">
					<h3 class="font-semibold text-white">Front-end Technical Lead — Best Buy</h3>
					<span class="text-sm text-gray-500">2017 – 2019</span>
					<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Engineered high-performance solutions for one of the top 10 eCommerce sites in North America. Scaled production apps handling thousands of requests per second.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border-l-2 border-pink pl-4">
					<h3 class="font-semibold text-white">Full-Stack JavaScript Instructor — DevLeague</h3>
					<span class="text-sm text-gray-500">2015 – 2017</span>
					<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-400">Taught full-stack JavaScript at one of the top 10 coding bootcamps worldwide. Created curriculum and prepared students for software engineering careers in Honolulu.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</details>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
